        Parameters:
        marker - specifies which position the play is put in
        player - indicates which player (X or O)

      • checkForWinner

        default boolean checkForWinner​(BoardPosition lastPos)
        this function will check to see if the lastPos placed resulted in a winner. If so it will return true, otherwise false. Passing in the last position will help limit the possible places to check for a win condition since you can assume that any win condition that did not include the most recent play made would have been caught earlier.
        Parameters:
        lastPos - the position of the last move
        Returns:
        whether or a not a play has won the game

      • checkForDraw

        default boolean checkForDraw()
        this function will check to see if the game has resulted in a tie. A game is tied if there are no free board positions remaining. You do not need to check for any potential wins because we can assume that the players were checking for win conditions as they played the game. It will return true if the game is tied and false otherwise.
        Returns:
        whether the two players have tied or not
